eir cross-sectional distribution of earnings, particularly differences in the\nsize of the lower tail. We conclude that the data sets we have analyzed, which\ninclude many of the most important available, show little evidence of any\nsignificant trend in male earnings volatility since the mid-1980s.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 1 Feb 2022 19:04:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-02-03"}
